1 B. There is hereby established the Oklahoma Rural Hospitals
2 Funding Assistance Grant Program.
3 C. As used in the Oklahoma Rural Hospitals Funding Assistance
4 Grant Program Act of 2025: "Adequated medical care facilities" means
5 facilities that:
6 1. Would meet or meets the eligibility of a federally qualified
7 critical access hospital;
8 2. Are located in a town or municipality with fewer than five
9 thousand (5,000) population according to the most recent Federal
10 Decennial Census; and
11 3. Is owned by a public trust organized under the laws of this
12 state or by a town or municipality of this state.
13 D. The State Department of Health shall administer the Oklahoma
14 Rural Hospitals Funding Assistance Grant Program to support the
15 state purpose of ensuring the health and safety of the residents of
16 the state by facilitating adequate access to health care services in
17 rural areas of the state. Such grant program shall embody the
18 following procedures, criteria, and limitations:
19 1. The Department shall develop a rubric of analysis and
20 accompanying application process to identify and prioritize rural
21 areas for grant funding, where such populations are
22 disproportionately impacted from accessing adequate medical care
23 facilities, due to distance;
24
